!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

oil /ɔɪl/

(oiling,oiled,oils) 

1. N-MASS Oil is a smooth, thick liquid that is used as a fuel and for making the parts of machines move smoothly. Oil is found underground. 石油 

例： The company buys and sells about 600,000 barrels of oil a day. 这家公司一天买卖约六十万桶石油。 

例： ...the rapid rise in prices for oil and petrol. …石油和汽油价格的飙涨。 

2. V-T If you oil something, you put oil onto or into it, for example, to make it work smoothly or to protect it. 给某物上油 

例： A crew of assistants oiled and adjusted the release mechanism until it worked perfectly. 助手们给排放装置加了润滑油并做了调节，直到其运转良好。 

3. N-MASS Oil is a smooth, thick liquid made from plants and is often used for cooking. 植物油 

例： Combine the beans, chopped mint, and oil in a large bowl. 将豆子、剁碎的薄荷和植物油混在一个大碗里。 

4. N-MASS Oil is a smooth, thick liquid, often with a pleasant smell, that you rub into your skin or add to your bath. 润肤油; 沐浴液 

例： Try a hot bath with some relaxing bath oil. 试试用点儿放松身心的沐浴液洗个热水澡吧。 

5.  →  see also crude oil , olive oil 

6. to burn the midnight oil→see midnight

